---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { site } from "../site.config";

const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${site.name} handles your data: it doesn't. Your script stays in your browser and is never uploaded.`}
  path="/privacy/"
  noindex={false}
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] px-6 md:px-12 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        {site.name} is designed so that there is almost nothing to have a privacy
        policy about. The short version: <strong class="text-[var(--color-fg)]">your
        script never leaves your device, and we don't have a server that could
        receive it.</strong>
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">What we collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Nothing personal. {site.name} has no accounts, no login, and no backend
          database. We never receive, store, or transmit the text of your script.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Where your script lives</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Your script and your settings (speed, font size, mirror mode, etc.) are
          saved using your browser's <em>local storage</em> — a private store on your
          own device. It exists only so the tool remembers your work between visits.
          You can clear it any time with the “Clear” button or by clearing your
          browser's site data. It is never sent anywhere.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Analytics</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may use a privacy-respecting, aggregate analytics measurement to count
          page views and understand which features are used. It does not identify you
          and never has access to your script. If analytics is enabled it is loaded
          only on the production site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Hosting</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The site is served as static files by a content-delivery network. Like all
          web hosts, the CDN may process standard, non-identifying request logs (such
          as IP address and user agent) for security and reliability. We do not combine
          this with anything else or use it to identify you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} is a general-audience utility and is not directed at children
          under 13. Since we collect no personal data, none is knowingly collected from
          anyone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If this policy changes, the “last updated” date above will change with it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about privacy? Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>
          or see the <a href="/contact/" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
